title: Missing 10-year-old boy found safe, Cary police say
text:
Missing 10-year-old boy found safe, Cary police say 
Posted 24 minutes ago   More on this Find News Near Me 
Morrisville, N.C. â€” A 10-year-old boy who went missing from school on Monday was found safe and returned to his mother early Tuesday morning, according to Cary police. 
Khristian Joseph was last seen at 3:45 p.m. as he was leaving Pleasant Grove Elementary School on foot. Joseph is usually picked up in front of the school by a relative and does not walk home or ride the bus. 
Cary officials said Joseph was found around 4:45 a.m. Tuesday and returned safely to his mother about half an hour later. 
Authorities focused their search Monday night around the school and the woods behind it after Joseph was seen on surveillance video walking toward the woods. 
Police K-9 officers and fire department personnel assisted in the search. 
The Durham Police Department assisted in returning Joseph. Credits
